title: Millburn High School girls tennis earns top seed
text:
Millburn High School girls tennis earns top seed October 16, 2015 Last updated: Friday, October 16, 2015, 11:40 AM By Jim Connelly Buy this photo staff photo by jim connelly 
Two-time defending champion Millburn High School has been awarded the top seed for the New Jersey State Interscholastic Athletic Association Girls Tennis Tournament of Champions. 
Millburn, the Group 3 champion, and Group 2 champion and No. 2 seed Holmdel High School drew byes into the semifinals. 
The T of C begins on Sunday, Oct. 18, with two first round matches. All T of C matches take place at the Garden State Tennis Center in Edison. 
Fourth-seeded Montgomery High School opposes fifth-seeded Academy of the Holy Angels at 3 p.m. 
Montgomery is the Group 4 champion. Holy Angels is the Non-Public A champion. 
Third-seeded Newark Academy take on sixth-seeded Shore Regional High School in a match scheduled to begin at 5 p.m. 
Newark Academy is the Non-Public B champion. Shore Regional is the Group 1 titlist. 
Holmdel will face the Newark Academy/Shore Regional winner in the first semifinal Tuesday, Oct. 20, at noon. 
In the day's second semifinal, Millburn will take on the Montgomery/Holy Angels winner. That match is scheduled for 2 p.m. 
The T of C final is scheduled for Wednesday, Oct. 21, at 2 p.m. 
Millburn is seeking match Newark Academy's record of eight T of C crowns.
